        </strong> With Bitcoin hitting a record $107,000, London-based Nickel Digital Asset Management <a href="https://www.hedgeweek.com/nickel-digital-sees-surge-in-interest-as-bitcoin-hits-record-highs/" target="_blank">reports</a> soaring institutional investor interest. Nickel's flagship Diversified Alpha fund posted over 30% year-to-date performance, while its AUM surged 115% in 2024. First-time institutional investors, previously hesitant about digital assets, are now exploring opportunities. </p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Hedge funds expect bonuses to skyrocket:
         </strong> 
         Hedge fund professionals <a href="https://www.hedgeweek.com/hedge-funds-bullish-on-bonus-increases/#:~:text=Hedge%20fund%20professionals%20are%20anticipating,%2Don%2Dyear%20on%20average." target="_blank">anticipate</a> a 65% bonus hike in January 2025, outpacing the global 50% average, according to eFinancialCareers. Private credit funds are particularly optimistic, with 91.3% forecasting increases, compared to just 26.6% for traditional asset managers. The Gulf region leads globally with a projected 78% jump, while UK bonuses rise 43%, driven by relaxed caps.</p>
        </mj-text>

