         <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Slow Ventures lowers fundraising goals:</strong>   
           Slow Ventures, known for backing Robinhood and Slack, is <a href="https://pitchbook.com/news/articles/slow-ventures-robinhood-fund-launch-vc#:~:text=Its%20latest%20fundraise%20appears%20to,will%20be%20realized%20in%20full." target="_blank">targeting</a> $165 million for its sixth fund—15% below its 2022 raise. The firm is also seeking $110 million for its third opportunity vehicle. Led by Facebook alums Sam Lessin and Kevin Colleran, Slow Ventures focuses on early-stage consumer and healthcare investments.</p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Venture firms pledge clean capital:</strong>   
           Over 20 VC firms, including Marlinspike and Snowpoint Ventures, have <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/12/19/over-20-venture-firms-pledge-to-not-take-money-from-china-russia/" target="_blank">signed</a> the Clean Capital Certification, vowing not to accept funding from adversarial nations like China and Russia. Spearheaded by Future Union, the pledge aims to protect critical technologies from foreign interference. While the initiative lacks formal vetting, it signals growing industry accountability. Defense-focused VCs are prominent signatories, with broader adoption expected to address concerns over national security and ethical investing in the tech sector.</p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Menlo, Anthropic invests in 18 AI startups:</strong>   
           Menlo Ventures and Anthropic have <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/12/18/menlo-ventures-and-anthropic-have-picked-the-first-18-startups-for-their-100m-fund/" target="_blank">picked</a> 18 startups for their $100 million Anthology Fund, with more in stealth mode. The selected ventures span fintech, radiology, cybersecurity, and AI applications like autonomous coding. Each startup receives $100,000+ in investments and $25,000 in Anthropic credits. This incubator-style program emphasizes AI app development beyond foundational models, aligning with 2025's projected boom in next-gen AI tools.</p>
        </mj-text>

